on the pig's back
Homonym Number:
Word Class:phrase
Sense Number:
Definition:successful, in a comfortable position, well off (in money, situation, etc.) cf. high on the hog
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1945 He was on the pig's back for the rest of his life when his father left all that money.
